Claude Fable 5 on 2026-07-17 at ~04:20:
All five fixes are in, verified end to end —desktop behavior is untouched (the signet rect is pixel-identical to the old source at 1024×768, 1440×900 and 1920×1080, zero console errors), so the gallery stays as it is. sources/current/ is refreshed and ready to deploy.

**Day by default.** The page no longer consults prefers-color-scheme: a first visitor always lands on day. Night comes only from the visitor's own toggle, and setNight already writes every flip to localStorage —so the preference persists whichever side it is finally left on, day included. (The gallery's night-capture seeding still boots night —verified.)

**Two taps on the contact icons.** On hoverless devices (matchMedia (hover: none) —every phone; mouse browsers skip the whole block) the first tap now only ARMS the icon: it wears the hover dress —gold and the 1px lift— through an .armed class, and the link does not fire; the second tap follows it, and tapping anywhere else disarms. Verified with emulated touch: first tap armed without navigating, second tap navigated to t.me/jonatanbb, an outside tap disarmed. Desktop hover/click is untouched —the arming code never runs there.

**The glow disks —same medicine as the text.** Exactly as you guessed: the cast canvas was the last fixed, viewport-sized layer repainted against the live scroll, so the compositor beat it to every frame and the disks trailed. It is now PAGE-anchored like the cracks and the gold text: painted in page coordinates over the whole page (backed at a capped density —the layer is blurred anyway— with a pixel budget for very tall pages), so an already-painted disk rides the page pixel-perfect however late a frame lands. Each paint covers the viewport band plus a full viewport of overscan on each side; the logo's clip hole —the one viewport-tied thing on the layer— is refreshed per frame. Verified scrolled: disks in register on their points, the annulus clean of glow.

**Eccentricity eased to ~2x.** The viewport pin went from 1024 to 780 —about twice your phone's native width, so the page renders roughly a third larger than yesterday. Still safely above the site's 760px breakpoint, and still zero horizontal overflow (scrollWidth == 780, no band).

**The logo reads the screen's shape now.** Two corrections:
- Portrait (the phone upright): the vertical anchor was 34% of the viewport HEIGHT —fine on a desktop window, but a phone's layout viewport is ~1700px tall, which is what dumped the logo below the about bar with a logo's worth of blank above it. The anchor is now min(34vh, 26vw) —capped against the width, 26vw being what 34% yields on a desktop-shaped window— so the logo pairs with the hero exactly as in the browser composition: annulus fully above the about bar, and the lede's float spacer shrinking with it, so the copy takes its full column back. The lights-off page anchor follows the same formula.
- Very short viewports (the phone turned): under 560px of visible height the mark is resized to 30% of the screen's vertical range and seated by the top right corner, 15% of the height off the top and the same off the right —clear of the toggles row. Measured on an emulated 844×390 phone: annulus diameter exactly 0.30 of the height, both margins 54px. Rotating back and forth re-fits live —it hangs off the resize handler.

Also verified: the ignition still runs clean —the gather glow and the mid-pulse frame render exactly as the gallery shots— and night recall, the language switch, dragging and the dash-fragment fix are unaffected.


